      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAYNE CARGO (3) was strongly fancied last time and hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but could manage only second (19.57) at this track over 340m. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Makes plenty of appeal. MOTOR CITY BOMB (4) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing third behind Let's Go Champ (20.27) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Bold showing expected. LUMEAH MONTE (1) finds it hard to win. Finished in the minors latest when third (20.13) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Expected to feature. KUNG FU PANDA (2) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at his latest outing at this circuit.",
